NUMBER 2759
REGION 11
CHANNEL 44
DEEPCAVE
MINEC
NAME Volcanic shaft, recess
*DESCRIPTION_START
A deformity in the shaft wall makes a deep recess which is sheltered from much of the heat blasting up from below. Unlike the blistering temperature below, it is hot here but not lethally so. Looking up, it seems likely that the platform would pass very close to this recess if it were lowered into the shaft. From this point upwards, the walls of the shaft are too smooth to climb.
*DESCRIPTION_END
FIXED_LIGHT
EXIT D 2758
EXIT ABOVE 2775
IFITEM 5
        IFPREVERB GO 5
                ECHO PLAYER You jump over to the platform.
                ECHO OTHERS %N jumps over to the platform.
                MOVE 2776
                CLEARVERB
        ENDIF
ENDIF

ITEM 0 282 ADJ1=265 ADJ2=347 ADJ3=192

IFPREVERB OPEN 0
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
                ECHO PLAYER The panel is already open.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
                ECHO PLAYER You pull the panel open, revealing a circular hole in the floor of the recess.
                ECHO OTHERS %N pulls open a round white metal panel, revealing a circular hole in the floor of the recess.
                EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1
                NEWITEM 2 336 VAL2=2301 ADJ1=693
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFITEM 2
 IFPREVERB LOOK 2
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER The hole leads into a vertical shaft wide enough for someone to slide down it. The walls of the shaft seem to be of a glassine material, not any good for climbing at all. Jumping into it would probably be suicidal.
 ENDIF
 IFPREVERB JUMP -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You hop into the circular hole, hoping this isn't a big mistake...
        ECHO OTHERS %N jumps up and falls through the hole in the floor, plummeting to certain death.
        DISBAND
        MOVE 2301
        AFFECT 2301
        ECHO OTHERS %N arrives from above.
 ENDIF
 IFPREVERB GO 2
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You can't simply go through the hole, as it leads to a vertical drop. You think you can easily jump, though, and drop through it. Doing so might be quite sucidal without special protective measures, though.
        IFVAR RAC = 6
                ECHO PLAYER Or, of course, you could fly down, as you are a drakin, after all.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SKILL14 > 10
                ECHO PLAYER Of course, you can also cast the fly spell, which might work just as well.
        ENDIF
 ENDIF
 IFPREVERB SPIT 2
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER Some hidden instinct for decency makes you swallow your spittle instead.
        ECHO OTHERS %N swallows with a "glung!" sound.
        GMMSG %N just tried to spit into the shaft where other people were. How SICK.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

