NUMBER 2301
NAME Glass-walled shaft
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
EXIT ABOVE 2759
EXIT BELOW 2302
DROPLOC 2302

IFVAR FLYING ! 1
        IFVAR RAC ! 8
                ECHO PLAYER You fall through the steadily-widening glass shaft.
                ECHO OTHERS %N plummets past you.
                DISBAND
                MOVE 2302
                AFFECT 2302
                ECHO OTHERS %N comes shooting down from above.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START
The shaft widens dramatically as it descends, going from a space wide enough
for a single falling body at the very top to a quite roomy area within the
space of a few yards. The walls are actually quite pretty, glittering, well
polished glasslike material worked to almost perfect smoothness.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 420 ADJ1=693 ADJ2=143

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The walls are polished stone, the volcanic rock around you melted down by
heat more intense than currently exists, then ground, either by nature or
by outside agency, until it is as smooth as glass. You can see about half
an inch into the transluscent surface, after which its roughness resumes.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER The walls are far, far too smooth to climb.
        IFVAR FLYING = 1
                ECHO PLAYER You, of course, are flying, so this is not a problem.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAUGH -1
        CLEARVERB
        AFFECT 2759
        ECHO ALL You hear %n laughing uproariously.
        AFFECT 2301
        ECHO PLAYER You laugh uproariously, the sound echoing in all directions.
        ECHO OTHERS %N laughs uproariously, the sound echoing in all directions.
        AFFECT 2302
        ECHO ALL You hear %n laughing uproariously.
        AFFECT 2303
        ECHO ALL You hear %n laughing uproariously.
        AFFECT 2304
        ECHO ALL You hear %n laughing uproariously.
ENDIF

;
;

NUMBER 2302
NAME Glass-walled shaft
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
EXIT ABOVE 2301
EXIT BELOW 2303
DROPLOC 2303

IFVAR FLYING ! 1
        IFVAR RAC ! 8
                ECHO PLAYER You fall like a rock. Not a small rock, either. A big, heavy rock.
                ECHO OTHERS %N falls onward like a dead brick.
                DISBAND
                MOVE 2303
                AFFECT 2303
                ECHO OTHERS %N comes shooting down from above, looking a little worried.
                EQUAL INTNUM60 444
        ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START
The walls of the shaft are now out of reach, easily thirty feet away from
the center here. Above the reddish glow from the main lava tube continues to
provide a hint of illumination, while below only darkness awaits.
*DESCRIPTION_END


