NUMBER 2306
NAME Cave, glowing lichen
DEEPCAVE
EXIT BELOW 2305
EXIT ABOVE 2306
IFPREVERB ASCEND -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER Despite the echoes you can hear above, there is no room to fly there.
ENDIF
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
Light fills the upper half of this chamber, reflecting from the smooth
surface of the stone in waves which distort slightly even as you watch, rays
of soap-bubble rainbow illumination. Its source is a form of lichen growing,
and glowing, on every wall save the one which slopes down to the half
melted chamber below. A few bones and the remains of a crate or wooden
pallet have been lashed together and wedged into a crack in the stone
floor, forming a rough, faded sign.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 204
EXTEND 0 lashed together from two hip-bones and a few old boards

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The sign seems to be quite old, created in haste or by someone with no real
skill at such lashings. The bones, you note, are hollow through the middle.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
Lava flow cut me off. May not escape, my burns. Slightly delirious. Will
try to stay in high area, out of lava's reach. Goblins say they will feed
me. Three passages, all lead to their shrine, but middle one higher. Losing
cohered mental now. Lichen on walls.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 83 VAL2=2305 ADJ1=821 ADJ2=312

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The walls are fairly rough, especially in the southwest of the cave, where
you could easily climb down to the area below. You note that there are three
passages spread across the opposite half of the area, the stone around their
entrances almost completely covered in the strange lichen.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFVERB LICK 1
        ECHO PLAYER The lichen growing on the wall makes it taste even worse than you expected, but then again, it doesn't seem poisonous.
        IFVAR FLYING ! 1
                SPELL 224 50
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CAST 1
        IFVAR SPELLNUM = 400
                CLEARVERB
                EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
                ECHO OTHERS %N gestures at a rough-textured stone wall.\The lichen on the wall glows faintly.
                ECHO PLAYER You gesture at a rough-textured stone wall.\The lichen on the wall glows faintly.
                ECHO PLAYER You sense that licking the wall can release the magic, disgusting as it seems.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

ITEM 2 73 VAL2=2309

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
This passage is to your left as you face the wall with the three set into
it. It seems narrower than the other two.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 3 73 VAL2=2307

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
Situated between two other passages, this one slopes sharply up as soon as
it leaves the main part of the cave behind. None of the glowing lichen grows
within it, leaving its reaches dark and shadowy.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 4 73 VAL2=2313
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
Sloping downwards slightly, this third passage is wider than the others.
*DESCRIPTION_END



