EXIT U 2308

;
;

NUMBER 2308
NAME Stone ledge, cairn
DARKNESS
DEEPCAVE

*DESCRIPTION_START
Rocks and chunks of pumice have been piled together here, blocking passage
along the ledge to the north. They plainly cover a body from the general
shape and size of the pile. A larger stone, resting atop the rest and aiding
them in stability, has been inscribed with a single rune in red pigment.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT ABOVE 2308
IFPREVERB ASCEND -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER There's nowhere to ascend to.
ENDIF

EXIT BELOW 2310

IFPREVERB DIG -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You aren't THAT hungry.
ENDIF

EXIT D 2307

ITEM 0 1397
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Aside from the red rune traced on its highest point, this cairn is nothing
more than a large pile of fist-sized stones covering someone's final resting
place. It's quite difficult to dig graves in stone, of course.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 238 ADJ1=259
EXTEND 1 traced upon the cairn
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The rune seems similar to murgish writing you have seen, though not the same.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB READ 1
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR SKILL32 < 3
                ECHO PLAYER The rune seems similar to murgish writing you have seen.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SKILL32 > 2
                ECHO PLAYER It resembles the murgish rune for "swordsmith".
        ENDIF
        IFVAR RAC = 5
                ECHO PLAYER Yes, you're quite sure that it's like the murgish rune for "swordsmith".]
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFTOUCH 0
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! TIM
        IFVAR FLAG1 ! 11
                EQUAL FLAG1 11
                PLREVENT 1
                CONTPLREVENT
                ECHO PLAYER You sense something within the stones of the cairn.
                IFVAR SKILL30 > 4
                        ECHO PLAYER Possibly something capable of communication, with the right assistance, you think...
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CAST 0
        IFVAR SPELLNUM = 311
                IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! TIM
                        CLEARVERB
                        EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
                        ECHO PLAYER You gesture at a cairn.
                        ECHO OTHERS %N gestures at a cairn.
                        EQUAL ITEMVAL1 TIM
                        PLREVENT 1
                        CONTPLREVENT
                        ECHO ALL A voice issues forth from beneath the stones of the cairn, "Trust not the family Gilnaerd. They betray! They betray!"
                        PLREVENT 1
                        CONTPLREVENT
                        ECHO ALL The voice continues, muffled, "They hired me to find special ores for their weapons... and now dead am I. They did not come for my body."
                        PLREVENT 1
                        CONTPLREVENT
                        ECHO ALL The voice concludes, "Never trust a noble! All of them want only their own desires..."
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
ENDIF

