NUMBER 2309
NAME Narrow passage, fissure walls
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS

*DESCRIPTION_START
Caught between two irregular walls of hardened lava, you cannot help but look
at them and speculate on their origin. Like the cracks which open in the ground
when an earthquake strikes, you imagine, these passages were formed when the
volcano was more active, literally tearing apart large masses of stone without
the resulting fissure ever coming close to the surface.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT S 2306
EXIT NW 2310

IFVERB RECALL -1
        IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
                ECHO PLAYER Such fissures have been known to close just as suddenly as they opened. It's a relief to realize that this one has been around for many years and is probably permanent... probably.
        ENDIF
ENDIF


