NUMBER 2325
NAME Lavafall's crest
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
You can see much here but you can hear hardly anything. The lava flow widens
in the last length of its channel, probably growing much more shallow as well,
before plunging off a ledge and into the depths below. Despite its relatively
small volume- a waterfall of equal size would make much les noise- it is too
loud to easily believe, the weight and density of the molten rock revealed in
the way it makes its moving presence known. Looking out past the falls you
can see little through the glare, just an open cave with no bottom, a rough
pit striking out for the center of the world.
*DESCRIPTION_END

