lip above where it spills across impermanent lumps of itself as it approaches
the state it is in now. Reduced by the small distance and the all-surrounding
scarlet light to a bar of white-seeming light, it stretched away down past the
vanishing point. The ledge, meanwhile, seems warm but not uncomfortably so,
and the way is easy. Some force seems to keep you from reaching its more
dangerous inner edge.
