NUMBER 2337
NAME Lava spill, outcropping
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
This outcropping, formed by the same lava flows which created the "hand"
formation below, is distinguished from a thousand others like it by two
things, its easy accessibility from the main ledge probably being the cause
of the second, which is an iron staff driven into a crack in the cavern
wall. The staff is not rusted at all, but is weathered and slightly bent.
*DESCRIPTION_END

