NUMBER 2338
NAME Lava spill, stairway
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
In the light from the falling lava stream and the reflection from the mists
filling the air below you see a short but wide stairway leading down from this
point, doubling back on the path currently traced by the ledge. At its bottom
is a round area, the ledge's actual ending.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 1226 VAL2=2339

EXIT NE 2336

;
;

VARIABLE BPPLAT
VARIABLE POPLAT
VARIABLE DOPLAT

NUMBER 2339
NAME Lava spill, ledge ends
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
Whoooooooooooooooooaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaoooooooooooooooooooooooooooooommmmm.
The sound of the lava striking the water's surface in the mist-shrouded, redlit
cavern below is a constant, unceasing roar which vibrates in your bones as much
as it resonates in your ears. It reverberates from the far wall of the spillway
and from this nearer one, off the circular outcropping and the stairway leading
up to the main ledge.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 6
                ECHO GROUP A stone platform, thirty feet across and six thick, floats in the air just beside the ledge.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY NOTHO_TATHER_TOLU
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 6
                ECHO PLAYER You speak the words, though the platform is already here.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT ! 6
                AFFECT 2340
                EQUAL POPLAT PLRSINROOM
                ECHO ALL You sense the platform shiver slightly as the words "Notho Tather Tolu" echo down from above. You sense that unless someone speaks the words on the platform itself, though, it will not alter its current course.
                AFFECT 2339
                IFVAR POPLAT > 0
                        ECHO PLAYER You sense that the platform has someone on it, and that it will obey them before it obeys your own commands.
                ENDIF
                IFVAR POPLAT = 0
                        ECHO PLAYER You sense a reaching within you, and feel the stone platform below respond.
                        EQUAL DOPLAT 1
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY SLOTHES
        ECHO PLAYER You sense that only someone on the platform can stop it with the word.
ENDIF

ITEM 0 81 VAL2=2338

IFITEM 1
        IFPREVERB GO 1
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO OTHERS %P steps onto the large stone platform.
                MOVEGROUP 2340
                AFFECT 2340
                ECHO OTHGROUP %P comes onto the platform from the ledge.
        ENDIF
        IFPREVERB LOOK 1
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER The platform is right beside the ledge. Despite its lack of support it seems stable enough to hold you up.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

;
;

NUMBER 2340
NAME Hovering stone platform
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
EXIT ABOVE 2339

*DESCRIPTION_START
The edges of the round piece of basalt have no guard rails or other means of
keeping passengers from tripping and falling to their deaths, inclining you
to stay near the center when possible. Every inch of the platform is covered
with tiny, intricate carvings, magical runes and strings of sentences in a
language you do not recognize. All around you is mist, a mist turned bright
red by the lava light streaming through its center, but you can gaze out
through it without trouble.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFSAY NOTHO_TATHER_TOLU
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 6
                ECHO PLAYER You say the words, although the platform is currently at its highest point, with the ledge to the north.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT ! 6
                ECHO PLAYER You feel the platform respond to your words and thoughts.
                EQUAL DOPLAT 1
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY TATHER_TOLU_STHARE
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 0
                ECHO PLAYER You say the words, although the platform is currently at the bottom of its course already, with a boulder to the south.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT ! 0
                ECHO PLAYER You feel the platform respond to your words and thoughts.
                EQUAL DOPLAT -1
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY SLOTHES
        IFVAR DOPLAT ! 0
                ECHO ALL The platform lurches to a halt!
                EQUAL DOPLAT 0
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFITEM 1
        IFPREVERB GO 1
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO OTHERS %P steps off the platform.
                MOVEGROUP ITEMVAL2
                AFFECT ITEMVAL2
                ECHO OTHGROUP %P steps off the platform.
                AFFECT 2340
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GAZE -1
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 6
                ECHO PLAYER You gaze at the ledge to the north, noting that the platform is at its highest point.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 5
                ECHO PLAYER You gaze at the mists and at the ledge a short distance above you.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 4
                ECHO PLAYER You are nowhere near the top or the bottom of the platform's course, but you can see the spreading panorama of a lake below you, a lake in a gigantic cavern, islands, some of large size, dark against the red-reflecting water.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 3
                ECHO PLAYER You can see directly down to the place where the lava hits the water from here, where it turns thousands of gallons of liquid into steam which cools to mist. The water churns and boils there, the sound louder than the actual noise of the impact.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 2
                ECHO PLAYER You note that the platform is not directly below the ledge, nor is it directly above an island. It seems to be en route between the two, moving horizontally.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 1
                ECHO PLAYER You gaze at the island below the platform, noting that a single stone building can be seen at its north end, surrounded by mud huts, as you pass overhead.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BPPLAT = 0
                ECHO PLAYER You gaze at the boulder to the south, noting to yourself that this is as low as the platform can go.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

;
;

