NUMBER 2344
NAME Small island, ritual flames
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
In the eternal red light and the depths of the cavern, it could always be
sunset or sunrise, late night or early morning. Thus are the flames kept
burning at all time, throwing a healthy yellow glow across this end of the
island, burning large logs which goblins haul in from the shore. Huts are
clustered all around, though the most interesting thing is a stone building,
probably a temple, which squats solidly to the north. Its front is open,
allowing anyone to simply walk in or out without looking for a door.
*DESCRIPTION_END

