From this point on the shore of the goblin island you can see out across the
surface of the lake in several places, the mists swirling in permanent eddies
to form tunnels and corridors wide enough for small boats to pass through.
Islets of stone, much smaller than even this one, drift through the passages
of clear air from time to time, floating like irregular watercraft.
