NUMBER 2347
NAME Stone Ship
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
The interior of the little ship is surprisingly roomy, as though the goblin
creators intended it for the use of larger beings such as yourself. You realize
then that they did exactly that. The mist drifts by the boat, obscuring most of
your view over the side, but you can make out water and the pumice outriggers
which help keep the ship afloat and stable. Glittering like a sheet of tiny
diamonds, the fishskin sail holds every hint of the surface breeze.
