NUMBER 2349
NAME Gray shore
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS

*DESCRIPTION_START
More moss coats the stone here, making the surface slick and slippery, though
not dangerously so. Even more of it can be seen to the north, forming large
clumps the size of bushes on the north shore of the isle. The stone tower at
the island's center is backlit through the red-tinted mist here; it would be
