NUMBER 2350
NAME Gray island, tower
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS

*DESCRIPTION_START
The tower dominates the surrounding island only because there isn't much
to dominate, squatting fully twelve feet tall and ten feet across. Its shadow
falls to the west, a shadow cast in the constant red light from the far-off
lava fall. None of the moss which clings to the shore has made it up to
the center, leaving the stone clean and relatively dry.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT S 2348
EXIT W 2349
EXIT N 2351

ITEM 0 414 ADJ1=194
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The tower is a circular one, roughly, and seems to have been formed from a
single, huge block of volcanic pumice. Its top is protected by crenellations
too small to be anything but decorative, and no entrance is in evidence. But
then you look more closely, and see something that makes you doubt your own
eyes. There is a gate, a set of two together, right in front of you... but
it is only a few inches high. What you first took to be pits and cracks in
the rough stone surface you now see to be tiny windows... this is a mighty
fortress, just not on your own scale.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 68 VAL2=2352 CLOSED
EXTEND 1 less than six inches high
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The gate is less than six inches high, but is otherwise a standard defensive
portal, designed to keep out marauders and keep in the populace.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB OPEN 1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER The gate is not only locked, it seems thoroughly barricaded. It seems to open outward, but has no handle on this side.
ENDIF

IFVERB KNOCK 1
        ECHO ALL In spite of the effort at politeness the inhabitants of the tower do not open the gate.
ENDIF

ITEM 2 249 ADJ1=327
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Peering in through the window, which is at your own eye level, you behold
a grand hall in miniature scale. Drapery of gray and green- streamers of the
island's seaweed, you realize- are hung from every wall, many of them somehow
embroidered with crudely depicted scenes of battle. A tiny, tiny throne is
at the far end of the hall, where a mouselike creature sits, waving its
paws in the air and gesturing frantically in your direction. Other rodents
are spread out across the floor of the hall, milling wildly about. Some flee
your peering eye while others stand their ground, weapons as large as your
littlest finger at the ready.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFVERB TAP 2
        ECHO ALL You hear tiny screams and shrieks from within the tower.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
        CLEARVERB
        SKILLCHECK 5 -20 DUMMY1
        IFVAR DUMMY1 < 0
                ECHO PLAYER [Round: 5 sec]
                EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
        ENDIF
        IFVAR DUMMY1 >= 0
                ECHO OTHERS %N climbs up the side of the small tower.
                DISBAND
                MOVE 2353
                AFFECT 2353
                ECHO OTHERS %N climbs up to the roof with you.
                POSITION KNEEL
                ECHO PLAYER [Round: 5 sec]
                EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
        ENDIF
ENDIF

