NUMBER 2352
NAME Inside the tower, gatehouse
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
You shift and flow, your form not your own, compressed into a tiny gatehouse.
Small creatures like bipedal mice run this way and that, shrieking and trying
to drive you away with tiny tridents. Their weapons are usless against your
unsolid form, of course. The entire gatehouse is less than a foot on any side
and no certain exit is available save the gate; transforming into solid form
would undoubtedly result in your horrible mutilation and death, as you are
less dense and durable than the stone walls around you.
*DESCRIPTION_END

