NUMBER 2353
NAME Short tower, roof
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
There isn't much room up on top of the tower, but it does afford you a lovely
view to the south, where you can see the eternal fires of the goblin village
and make out the vague, uncertain outlines of the temple there. To the east you
can see through the mist surprisingly well, watching the superheated bar of
falling lava as it plunges into the water some miles distant. To the west is
only cold fog, but to the north, strangely, there are shallows of some kind,
clogged with the same clinging moss that covers this island.
*DESCRIPTION_END

